comments.text:
These flags are part of struct CERTRevocationTests:

    PRUint64 *cert_rev_flags_per_method;
    PRUint64 cert_rev_method_independent_flags;

They are passed to public API:

   PKIX_RevocationChecker_Create(
        PKIX_UInt32 leafMethodListFlags,
        PKIX_UInt32 chainMethodListFlags,
        ...);

VS2010 correctly warns that the use of these variables in these function calls results in truncation from 64-bits to 32-bits. 

These CERTRevocationTests members should be typed PKIX_Uint32 and we should ensure that all flags fit in a PKIX_Uint32 integer. If we cannot change the type of these members then we should add an explicit check at the call sites to ensure we are not discarding flags > UINT32_MAX unexpectedly.

